  "explanation": "The defendant, utilizing their position as an accountant, abused a high level of professional trust to embezzle $25,000. This breach of fiduciary duty warrants a period of incarceration to reflect the seriousness of the offense and promote respect for the law. However, significant mitigating factors are present: the defendant has no prior criminal record, has demonstrated remorse, and has made a good-faith effort to partially repay the stolen funds. Considering these factors, a sentence at the lower end of the typical range is appropriate, balancing rehabilitation and accountability.",
